<2ND_LINE>AM-Bar Shootings,0147</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Suspect Turns Himself In</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BUTLER, Pa. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A father of 11 was charged with murder Monday
in connection with what police said was an unprovoked Father's Day
shooting spree at a bar.
   Robert Edward McLaughlin, 51, of Glenshaw, turned himself in to
Shaler Township police one hour after Brett Stidham, 22, of
Pittsburgh, died Monday at Presbyterian-University Hospital in
Pittsburgh.
   State police said McLaughlin opened fire Sunday night inside the
Plainview Bar in Penn Township, shooting Stidham and three others
before fleeing in a pickup truck. Investigators said they believe
McLaughlin didn't know his victims.
   In addition to murder, McLaughlin was charged with attempted
murder and aggravated assault. One of the three shooting survivors
was critically injured, another was hospitalized in fair condition
and the third was treated and released.
   District Justice Frank Wise ordered McLaughlin jailed without
bond.
