<1ST_LINE>d a PM-HealthClubTax     06-21 0149</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Health Club Tax,0151</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Court Says Chicago Health Club Tax is Unconstitutional</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SPRINGFIELD, Ill. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Chicago's ``yuppie tax'' on racquetball
and health club memberships violates the state constitution's
restriction on occupation taxes, the state Supreme Court has ruled.
   The city needs approval from the state legislature to impose its
4 percent levy on club membership fees, the court said Monday.
   ``The city has gone far beyond merely taxing particular
activities and has imposed a tax unique to those types of
commercial enterprises,'' Justice Joseph Cunningham wrote in the
opinion.
   The court also said that the tax could not be viewed as a valid
levy on amusements since the clubs offer a wide variety of
non-amusement activities such as nutrition instruction and diet
counseling.
   The decision reversed an appellate court ruling but affirmed a
circuit court decision in a case brought by a group of Chicago
health clubs.
</TEXT>
