<2ND_LINE>AM-Not Dead,0190</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Cancer Patient Thought to be Dead Awakens in Mortuary</HEAD>
<DATELINE>HARARE, Zimbabwe (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A cancer patient who was pronounced dead
in the hospital awoke later in a mortuary, and she said her
superstitious relatives were afraid to visit her, it was reported
Tuesday.
   The family of Beauty Shitto had made funeral arrangements to
bury her after doctors at the hospital in Gweru, 160 miles
southwest of Harare, declared her dead and sent her body to the
mortuary, the semi-official Zimbabwe Inter-African News Agency
reported.
   The relatives slaughtered a cow and a goat for the funeral
feast, the news agency reported.
   Mrs. Shitto told the news agency that she awoke ``in a certain
small room'' in the mortuary.
   Her sister, Margaret, ran away in fear when she saw her alive
and other relatives were sympathetic but ``nervous,'' Mrs. Shitto
said.
   ``My death and subsequent rising from the dead baffled
everyone,'' she said. ``I cannot remember anything that happened
while I was dead.''
   ZIANA said Health Ministry officials confirmed the incident but
declined to say how long she was unconcious in the mortuary.
</TEXT>
