<HEAD>With AM-Superfund</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Here are the sites proposed for deletion from
those proposed earlier for the National Priority List for
``Superfund'' toxic waste cleanups by the Environmental Protection
Agency.
   The agency said these sites generally are part of an
installation holding a permit under the federal hazardous waste
law, although they may not be actively handling waste. Cleanups are
better handled by the owner under that law, although nothing
prevents use of Superfund later if it should prove desirable, EPA
said.
   In addition, the agency deleted three sites from the list in
April because work had been completed or there was no longer a
threat from them. They were the Mountain View Mobile Home Estates
in Globe, Ariz.; the Middletown Road Dump in Annapolis, Md.; and
the Harris Site on Farley Street in Houston, Texas.
