<HEAD>Spain's Gonzales Might Be Invited To Paris At Time of Next Summit</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TORONTO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   President Francois Mitterrand said Tuesday he
might invite Spain's Premier Filipe Gonzales to Paris next July at
the time of next year's economic summit.
   At a news conference, Mitterrand was asked if Spain might be
added to the seven summit nations next year.
   The French president did not answer directly, but said that
Gonzales and several other leaders might be asked to visit Paris
for the July 14, 1989, celebrations of the bicentennial of the
French Revolution _ which happens to coincide with the summit.
   Officials in the summit delegations consider highly unlikely any
expansion of the group's membership, which now consists of the
United States, Japan, Britain, France, West Germany, Italy, Canada
and the European Economic Community.
