<HEAD>Rockwell International Pleads Innocent to Overbilling Charges</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Rockwell International Corp. and two former
executives pleaded innocent Tuesday to federal charges accusing the
aerospace contractor of overbilling the Air Force by $450,000.
   The pleas were entered in a hearing before U.S. District Judge
Consuelo B. Marshall, who set trial for Oct. 11.
   A seven-count indictment filed earlier this month names Rockwell
and two former managers at the Seal Beach Satellite Systems
division, Donald H. Carter, 59, and Robert Zavodnik, 46, with
overbilling on a navigation system contract.
   Thomas Holliday, a Rockwell attorney, declined to comment on the
case.
