<HEAD>World International To Acquire Omni Hotels</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Omni Hotels Group, a chain of 39 hotels in the
United States and Mexico, will be sold for $135 million to World
International Limited and The Wharf Limited, the companies
announced Tuesday.
   The transaction is expected to be completed before the end of
July, the companies said in a joint news release.
   Omni Hotels, owned by the Irish airline Aer Lingus since 1976,
is the 14th largest hotel chain in the United States. Among its
properties are the Omni Berkshire Place in New York, the Omni
Parker House in Boston and Chicago's Omni Ambassador East.
   World International and The Wharf head a major group of nine
companies in Hong Kong and Singapore, with interests in hotels,
real estate, transportation and retailing. The World group owns and
manages Marco Polo International Hotels in the Far East.
</TEXT>
