<HEAD>London Stocks Rise</HEAD>
<NOTE>EDS: UPDATES throughout with closing index; no pickup.</NOTE>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Share prices jumped on Tuesday to finish near the
session's highest levels, but analysts had trouble explaining the
rise.
   The Financial Times-Stock Exchange 100-share index was up 16.1
points, or 0.9 percent, at 1,860.1, at the close, fractionally
below its best level for the day of 1,860.2.
   Trading volume amounted to 380.2 million shares, slightly better
than Monday's 323.6 million shares.
   ``It seems to me as if the market is simply showing that it
wants to move higher at this point,'' said one analyst.
   The market has been able to ``resist bad news and refuses to go
down very far,'' said Charles Larkham, an equity analyst with James
Capel & Co.
   ``It's very encouraging that London is moving higher without the
stimulus coming from either New York or Tokyo,'' he said.
</TEXT>
