<HEAD>Tomkins To Acquire Murray Ohio In Friendly Deal</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: ADDS 2 new grafs after 2nd graf pvs to UPDATE with Electrolux
dropping its tender offer; uppicks 3rd graf pvs: ``Murray Ohio ...</NOTE>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Tomkins PLC, a British industrial holding company,
said Tuesday it has agreed to acquire Tennessee-based Murray Ohio
Manufacturing Co., the target of a hostile bid from AB Electrolux
of Sweden, for $224 million.
   Tomkins will pay $56 dollars a share for the U.S. maker of
lawnmowers and bicycles, topping a $52-a-share bid from Electrolux
that Murray Ohio's board rejected as inadequate.
   Meanwhile, a spokesman for AB Electrolux said that in view of
the merger announcement, it is terminating its tender offer for
Murray Ohio.
   ``We thought our all-cash offer of $52 per share was fully
priced, and we are not willing to pay a higher price,'' the
spokesman said.
   ``Murray Ohio is a typical Tomkins acquisition ... with strong
brands in stable markets,'' said Tomkins Chief Executive Gregory
Hutchings.
   He also pointed to Murray Ohio's ``unrealized potential'' and
said the acquisition should ``produce enhanced growth in earnings
per share for Tomkins.''
   Tomkins, which changed its name from F.H. Tomkins PLC earlier
this year, already has interests in the lawnmower business in
Britain through its Hayters PLC and Beaver Equipment Ltd. units.
   The acquisition of Murray Ohio would be Tomkins' second purchase
in the United States after its $112.5 million acquisition of Smith
& Wesson Corp., the U.S. gun manufacturer, from Lear Siegler
Holdings Corp. a year ago.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
